      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHEZA CARONA (6) is a talented mare who has managed two wins and two minor placings from four starts this time in work. Produced another fine effort last start when she finished third over 1609m at Port Pirie, beaten 4.5 metres. Meeting a deeper field this time but she is up to the challenge. DON CAPITANO (1) resumes after great success last prep, winning on two occasions and culminating in a seventh over 1800m at this track on November 3. Has the benefit of a good draw. Sure to prove hard to beat on his return. NEED ME SOME SUGAR (5) is on the radar after her last-start fourth over 1800m at this track a week ago. SKINNY HORACE (3) has been about the mark of late and must be respected, the latest offering a sound third at this track over 1800m.",
